14
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:38,480
It won’t actually land on the moon,

15
00:00:38,480 --> 00:00:42,690
but it will help with the landing process
for a future craft.

16
00:00:42,690 --> 00:00:45,680
China’s military-led space program wants
to be

17
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:48,430
the first to land on the far side of the moon.

18
00:00:48,430 --> 00:00:51,710
It’s sometimes also called the dark side
because

19
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:55,370
that side always faces away from the Earth.

20
00:00:55,370 --> 00:00:58,420
The new relay satellite would help solve the
issue of communication.

21
00:00:58,420 --> 00:01:02,469
So, if China does manage to make it to the
dark side of the moon

22
00:01:02,469 --> 00:01:03,500
later this year,

23
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:08,820
they’ll be the first to get a clear view
of when the Decepticons attack.

24
00:01:08,820 --> 00:01:10,670
But Chinese technological breakthroughs

25
00:01:10,670 --> 00:01:13,520
aren’t just going to the dark side of the
moon.

26
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:18,000
The dark side of technology has also arrived
in China.

27
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,750
Chinese authorities just arrested

28
00:01:19,750 --> 00:01:22,600
a dangerous fugitive by the name of Yu

29
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:26,310
at the concert of famous Hong Kong singer
Jacky Cheung,

30
00:01:26,310 --> 00:01:30,240
whose nickname is the God of Songs.

31
00:01:30,240 --> 00:01:33,530
How did police find the man in that crowd?

32
00:01:33,530 --> 00:01:34,549
Simple.

33
00:01:34,549 --> 00:01:37,020
Facial recognition software picked out his
face

34
00:01:37,020 --> 00:01:39,009
as his entered the venue.

35
00:01:39,009 --> 00:01:41,640
Local police wrote on their WeChat account,

36
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:44,920
“Wearing a smile as he came to see his idol,

37
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:48,090
he hadn’t realized that he was already being
watched.”

38
00:01:48,090 --> 00:01:49,090
Hahaha.

39
00:01:49,090 --> 00:01:50,090
Haha.

40
00:01:50,090 --> 00:01:51,090
Ha.

41
00:01:51,090 --> 00:01:53,840
That’s not creepy.

42
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:57,500
They’d been watching for him for 3 years.

43
00:01:57,500 --> 00:02:01,680
And get this—this is the third time in two
months

44
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:04,549
that a fugitive was caught this way...

45
00:02:04,549 --> 00:02:06,930
at a Jacky Cheung concert.

46
00:02:06,930 --> 00:02:07,980
Wait a minute.

47
00:02:07,980 --> 00:02:10,419
Is Jacky Cheung a secret crimefighter

48
00:02:10,419 --> 00:02:12,129
known as the God of Songs

49
00:02:12,129 --> 00:02:16,700
whose superpower is luring criminals to his
concerts?

50
00:02:16,700 --> 00:02:18,959
That would explain so much.

51
00:02:18,959 --> 00:02:22,060
So what was the heinous crime Yu committed

52
00:02:22,060 --> 00:02:24,780
that got him arrested at the concert?

53
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:27,890
He owed almost 20,000 dollars...

54
00:02:27,890 --> 00:02:30,650
on unpaid potatoes.

55
00:02:30,650 --> 00:02:33,199
That’s no small potatoes.

56
00:02:33,199 --> 00:02:35,969
Ah ha ha.

57
00:02:35,969 --> 00:02:36,969
Wait,

58
00:02:36,969 --> 00:02:41,499
what use could anyone have for 20,000 dollars
worth of potatoes?

59
00:02:41,499 --> 00:02:44,120
Perhaps it’s the God of Songs’ archnemesis...

60
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:46,430
Chairman Potato Head?

61
00:02:46,430 --> 00:02:50,219
Anyway, these kinds of arrests using facial
recognition

62
00:02:50,219 --> 00:02:52,209
will happen more and more.

63
00:02:52,209 --> 00:02:54,699
The Chinese Communist Party has invested heavily

64
00:02:54,699 --> 00:02:57,449
in AI-powered surveillance cameras.

65
00:02:57,449 --> 00:02:58,449
Within three years,

66
00:02:58,449 --> 00:03:00,969
they plan to add 400 million new cameras

67
00:03:00,969 --> 00:03:04,169
capable of recognizing and tracking citizens.

68
00:03:04,169 --> 00:03:08,159
They will also be able to identify your car
and your friends.

69
00:03:08,159 --> 00:03:13,079
Here’s another fun fact about China’s
facial recognition surveillance program.

70
00:03:13,079 --> 00:03:17,089
They’ve started installing it in schools
behind the blackboard

71
00:03:17,089 --> 00:03:19,829
to see how much kids are paying attention,

72
00:03:19,829 --> 00:03:23,120
tracking every movement of students’ pupils.

73
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:25,560
I know, that sounds disturbing,

74
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:28,439
especially if you’ve ever fallen asleep
in class.

75
00:03:28,439 --> 00:03:29,810
But don’t worry,

76
00:03:29,810 --> 00:03:32,920
the system can be fooled.

77
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,110
